The shadow JAR distributed by this project bundles relocated copies of the
following third-party libraries, which are themselves distributed under the
Apache License, Version 2.0:

  * OpenTelemetry Java (https://github.com/open-telemetry/opentelemetry-java)
      - opentelemetry-sdk
      - opentelemetry-sdk-metrics
      - opentelemetry-exporter-otlp
      - opentelemetry-runtime-telemetry-java17
    Relocated to: dev.monedula.metricsreporter.shaded.opentelemetry.*

  * gRPC Java (https://github.com/grpc/grpc-java)
    Relocated to: dev.monedula.metricsreporter.shaded.grpc.*

  * OkHttp (https://github.com/square/okhttp) and
    Okio  (https://github.com/square/okio)
    Pulled transitively by the OTLP HTTP exporter.
    Relocated to: dev.monedula.metricsreporter.shaded.okhttp3.*
                  dev.monedula.metricsreporter.shaded.okio.*

  * Kotlin standard library (https://github.com/JetBrains/kotlin)
    Pulled transitively by OkHttp.
    Relocated to: dev.monedula.metricsreporter.shaded.kotlin.*

  * JetBrains / IntelliJ Annotations
    (https://github.com/JetBrains/java-annotations)
    Pulled transitively by the Kotlin standard library.
    Relocated to: dev.monedula.metricsreporter.shaded.jetbrains_annotations.*
                  dev.monedula.metricsreporter.shaded.intellij_annotations.*

Each of those libraries retains the copyright of its respective authors. The
relocation of their packages is purely a classpath-conflict-avoidance measure
required for the plugin to load alongside Kafka's own dependency set; it does
not modify their source.

Apache License 2.0 text: https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0

The Apache Kafka client API and the legacy Yammer/Coda Hale metrics-core
registry that this plugin integrates against are NOT bundled — they are
expected to be supplied by the host Kafka broker or client process.
